race.description: Evergreen Turf Special Ballot Maiden Plate
race.comment: MOVE THE TORANA (11) brings strong provincial form to resumption. Has an awkward barrier but she can come back further improved. Kersley stays aboard suggesting she's ready to go. Well placed and happy to have her on top. WATT ON EARTH (6) was narrowly beaten at Donald and at Ballarat the one before. Drops back 200m but has the inside barrier and rates to be in the finish. PETROULA (15) peaks for the Dwyer stable and is still racing shy of her best efforts. John Allen goes aboard and she finally draws a reasonable barrier. MORAL TURPITUDE (16) fought on well placing at Donald. Hard-fit now and maps for a soft run. Each way claims.
